and I would wager to say more powerful than the other classes.  However, this would throw off game balance (in the opposite direction that it is now) so it's simply not feasible.  But, I do enjoy discussing ideas how Verant (if they were willing) might go about improving us. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Aside from the obvious whining and inter-class animosity this idea would create, how about moving the mana-regen-improvement line of spells from enchanters to wizards?  Verant seems to not want to put any work into game enhancements and changing which class that can cast a spell would certainly not be hard.  Right now, it seems that enchanters have two major group-desirable roles: 1/ Crowd control and 2/ Improving mana-regen.  With respect to crowd control, enchanters are unequalled and I think they do great at it (with exceptions, of course *grin*).  This would give us a way to contribute to our group and it would enhance our own mana-regeneration in all cases (we'd always have Clarity *cheer*).  As far as game mechanics goes, the spell is already present in the game and, if anything, this would make the average group less powerful because they would require two characters where they have one now.  Of course, this would improve our soloing as well, which would be a strong argument for Verant against this, but that's not the point of my post. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now, don't get me wrong... I think we all know a change like this would never actually be implemented (and there are many reasons for that as well) but I was more curious as to everyone's reaction here about whether it would &quot;fix&quot; our situation or not without the drastic increase in raw power a real wizard should have (and hence without throwing out game balance too much).<br>
<br>
Dawn<br>
56th Evoker<br>
(actually there was alot more than 55 people Evoker before me, but I meant I'm 56th level *grin*) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoingo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oingo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 1:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well....</span><hr size=1> VI has stated , and wizards in general have agreed, that we will not get a Clarity line of spells. That is a Chanter role. (and don't forget speed too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
However, I am of the school of thought that some form of mana-regen increase for us is the only fix we need, albeit a LARGE increase.<br>
<br>
 That said.....Why are there NO Wizard only Flowing thought V-X items?? wouldn't that be cool =) a stackable 5-10 mana/per tick item or 2 would be nice.....sigh  <p>55 Evoker 
