Current Player of PSO, CS,  and many other better games :-P<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uakailen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akailen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 6:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaddya think of this idea?</span><hr size=1> Greetings!<br>
<br>
Well, as an enchanter, I can tell you that taking mana regen spells away from the enchanters and giving them to the wizards wouldn't go over too well (no one wants to lose any of their power).  However, it wouldn't bother me in the slightest if wizards got some form of mana regen spells that were stackable with mine, not stackable with mine, or even better than mine, but please don't make me give up my Breeze, Clarity, etc. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Also, I have heard from several wizards that they don't want to be buffers, they want to do damage and lots of it.  I think one thing that is really hurting wizards now is their root and snare spells.  If wizards didn't have these two spells, then damage could be increased without the fear of wizards having the audacity to solo.  Please Note:  I am NOT proposing wizards lose these spells, so no fireballs please!  At the any ratre, nice chatting! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Akailen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulanlaornplaneswalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LanlaornPlaneswalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 7:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaddya think of this idea?</span><hr size=1> Wizard Mana Regen should NOT be a spell, we're not buffers.<br>
<br>
Wizard Mana Regen should NOT be an item, items balance melee classes not casters.<br>
<br>
Wizard Mana Regen SHOULD be a innate regen. Similar to Iksar and Troll HP regen, this innate mana regen boost would obviously stack with clarity and help only the Wizard, which Verant seems to be so intent on.<br>
<br>
Also, like the Iksar and Troll HP regens it could scale up with level, so as not to be overpowering at lower levels and useless at upper levels.<br>
<br>
 <p>Lanlaorn Planeswalker<br>
Wizard Extraordinare<br>
Champion of Marr<br>
<center>

<br>
"Planeswalking isn't about walking, its about falling and screaming"
<br> ----
<br>
"Yes, I think 'toast' is an appropriate description"
<br> ----
<br>
"Anybody want some... <i>toast</i>?"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 831<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 8:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaddya think of this idea?</span><hr size=1> Actually if they just made our DD and AE spells use 10-25% less mana and cast that much faster, for 10% or so more damage, we'd be much better off.  Cap it off by lifting the damage cap per level, and reducing recast time by half or less.  For example instead of Ice Comet looking like this:<br>
<br>
Ice Comet<br>
400 mana<br>
1110 damage +10/level (1 level)<br>
6.3 second casting time<br>
2.5 second recast time<br>
<br>
It would look like this:<br>
<br>
Ice Comet v.2<br>
300-360 mana<br>
1220 damage +10/level (1330 damage at level 60)<br>
4.75-5.5 second casting time<br>
1.5 second recast time<br>
<br>
Thats about 1 more burn at the first level you get it for around 100 more damage.  The max damage cap would allow our low level blasts to be steadily increasing but not overpowered (the most extreme example is 60 levels of +1 per level for Shock of Frost ... making it 63 damage at level 60 heheh).<br>
<br>
But we still face three basic problems:<br>
<br>
Aggro that doesn't allow you to burn very much nor often.<br>
<br>
Mana costs that suck our mana down so we can't blast very often (lowering mana costs would help this a lot, then group with mana recovery guys and get it back the same as now).<br>
<br>
Resists cut your damage down, and monsters percieve that damage as max, resulting in the aggro problem.<br>
<br>
Concussion sort of helps with the first, but its <br>
<br>
A) high level (39 out of 60)<br>
B) quest is too difficult<br>
<br>
And the third you get Lures for.... at higher than level 50.  Verant designed a class around something they don't really want to allow to be what it needs to be to justify focussing a class around, and that the game design doesn't really support well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dawntm>Dawn TM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/01 1:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaddya think of this idea?</span><hr size=1> Oh my... I think some of you misunderstood what I was meaning.  The reasons this is not feasible are many, including several that none of you have even mentioned.  I wasn't suggesting that Verant implement this, merely wishing to hear peoples thoughts on whether, if it WERE feasible, on whether this &quot;fix&quot; would be ample.  I don't want enchanters to lose any abilities - I know that would bug me a whole bunch if that happened to me and I were an enchantress.<br>
<br>
I do heartily agree with several of you regarding many things that were said.  I don't want to be a buffer.  I want to be group-desirable. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And how does my class be group desirable?  By doing obscene amounts of damage. *grin*  Yes, I agree our enhanced mana-regen should be an innate ability.  Or drastic decreases in mana-costs of spells.. that might work too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Grimstaff. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   In my extensive lurking, I would wager yours is the name that stands out the most, partly because I see it so often *grin* and partly because I so often agree with your posts.  Even with increased efficiency, there are other factors that limit us, which keep us in check, so to speak, when it comes to doing &quot;too much&quot; damage (whatever that means).  As far as Concussion goes, though, that's a quest I can't handle alone so I haven't got it.  Heard mixed reports about it, though, but mostly good. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just my ramblings.<br>
<br>
Dawn<br>
56th Evoker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/01 7:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whaddya think of this idea?</span><hr size=1> I agree with the people who want higher mana regen as something that's done without a buff.  Verant has also said they won't do ANYTHING about faster casting, or lowered mana costs, or anything which would increase our damage per second(though they will probably give +200% haste items to melees before too much longer).<br>
<br>
I'd personally love to see an UNRESISTABLE root spell with a minimum duration for &quot;parking&quot; mobs.  None of this garbage of having it only work on certain mobs either.<br>
<br>
Stun spells that should work on all mobs would also help make us more useful.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 54 Wizard<br>
Call of Ascension<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=312.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=312.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General EQ Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm59">Gene